    		email: scot *at* cs *dot* dartmouth *dot* edu
                <p>
		<B>Research Interests:
		</B>
		<BR>
		My main research area is algorithms, primarily 
		computational geometry. Much of my work has dealt with 
		computing a structure called the Voronoi diagram and its 
		geometric dual, the Delaunay Triangulation. 
		I have also worked on Numerical Control (NC) machining.
                <p>
                Recently I have been working on approximating polygonal 
                chains by arcs and biarcs and finding properties of and
                algorithms to compute the farthest-segment Voronoi diagram.
		<P>
